The vast majority of these were sexually infected, which is a change from the past.
Traditionally, HIV spread rapidly to some parts of China as a result of infected blood transfusions.
However, the number of people contracting HIV in this way has been reduced almost entirely, Chinese health authorities said at a congress held in Yunnan province.
