The study, conducted by the National Trust for Scotland, will follow common bats and sopranos, as well as Daubenton’s riverside and long-eared brown bats from Inverewe Gardens in Wester Ross.
Special recorders will be placed at strategic locations on the property to track bat activities during the season.
