Bat populations in Scotland and the United Kingdom have declined considerably in the last century.
They are under threat from construction and development affecting their nests and the loss of their habitat.
Wind turbines and electrical wiring can also pose a risk to them, as can insecticide papers and other chemical treatments of building materials or attacks from domestic cats.
