It stresses the importance of checking for bats before carrying out maintenance tasks within the properties, since a breeding colony can be involuntarily destroyed and 400 females and young could be killed, which would mean annihilation of an entire local population.
Bats are protected and it is illegal to kill, harass or harass them, as well as destroy their colonies.
Elisabeth Ferrell, the Scottish officer in charge of the Bat Conservation Trust, has encouraged the public to collaborate.
